states of a thread / thread life cycle

1. NEW : Thread t = new Thread();
2. RUNNABLE : t.start(); thread instance given to scheduler for execution
3. RUNNING : when thread starts to run
4. BLOCKED : thread is temporarily inactive , ex. when lock is obtained on a resource by another thread causing a thread to block
5. WAITING : thread is waiting , ex waiting for notify from another thread, or waiting for a timeout period
6. DEAD : thread terminated after finishes execution
